{"/service/ndnp/ak/batch_ak_jaeger_ver01/data/sn87062169/00514154314/1930013101/0414.xml":{"full_text":"Smoard Yaiiu Um w an\nOF SEW AKD. A l, Asiv A KaU'bliftheb August l\u00bb. IWM\nPublished daily except Sunday by\nTHE HATE WAY PUBLISHING COMPANY\nEntered in the postofi iee at Seward, Alaaka mb\nsecond clans mail matter\nH. V. HOBEN and E. F. JESSEN, Proprietors\nE. F. Jessen, Editor and Manager\nMEMBER OF THE ASSOCIATED PRESS\nThe Associated Press is exclusively entitled to the use for republication of all\nnews dispatches credited to it or not otherwise in this paper and also the local new*\npublished herein.\nAll rights for republicatious of special dispatches herein are reserved.\nThis paper reserves the right to reject any advertisement it so desires.\nEastern Representatives American Press Association\nMember of the International Typograi-hicaw Union\nADVERTISING RATES\nPer single column, one to six issues, ia r inch .50\nPer single column inch, per month 3.50\nLegal Notice*, per line per issue \"\".I....\".\u201d.\u201d.\"\u201d..\u201d Aft\nClassified Advertisements, per line, per issue ......15\nNotice o\u00bb f inal Proof Notices 12.On\nhrtice to Creditors Noth ea 16.00\nSUBSCRIPTION RATES\nDally by carrier, per month 1.26\nDaily by mail, per month I 00\nDally by mail, per veilr \"ii\nWeekly Gateway by mail, per year 3.50\nHAIL A HARDY MARINER\nMany people have congratulated Captain Heinie\nBerger and his good ship Discoverer on ms new con\ntracts for carrying the United States mail along the\nhighways and byways from the Port of Seward, Cook\nInlet to Anchorage, but we are wondering wnetner\nCaptain Berger should be commiserated with and the\npeople he is to serve congratulated.\n\u201cCap\u201d has certainly picked out a nice bed of roses\nfor himself. He has picked out the roughest seas this\nside of Cape Horn and he proposes to make regular\ntrips that the far dwellers may keep in touch with the\nworld and know that there is still a U. S. A. He is stak\ning his life and his vessel against some government\nmoney, it is true, but if you know \u2018Cap\u2019 you will know\nthere is something more behind it. He is going into it\nbecause he loves the game and the hazvds and because\nhe is doing a real service for people who really need\nit\u2014a service that is given with a smile and a heartiness\nthat mask the real dangers and hardships that lay\nfore and aft, to starboard and to larboard.\nCaptain Berger isn\u2019t just an ordinary mail car\nrier. He spells transportation to the outlying places\nwith a capital \u201cT\u201d, and he has done more to improve\nthe morale of the isolated communities of Cook Inlet\nand the Iliamna country than any individual in recent\nyears.\nHe has done this because he will go a long ways out\nof his way to do some one a service not strictly called\ntor in the letter of his contract and for that reason the\npeople of the Inlet have come to rely on him for extra\nordinary performance. His weakness in saying \u2018No\u201d\nhas cost him a lot of trouble and money too, and he\nnearly lost his boat trying to do some one a favor, but\nhe comes up smiling and ready to tackle it again.\nAnu he has gone farther than that. He has improv\ned his ship until it is now one of the staunchest vessels\nin the northern waters; and he knows how to run it.\nHe has established contacts with towns and districts\nwhich insure the inhabitants thereof that at such and\nsuch a time they can move their mail, their goods or\nthemselves whither they might go.\nMany towns of Cook Inlet and the people of the II\niamsa had a tough time thru the past few years because\nof lack of service and they have frequently been cut\noff from the outside world for months at a time. Cap\ntain Berger has changed that. H? and his ship have\nbeen a great asset to all concerned\nThe Gateway is sincerely pleased and thankful\nthat \u201cCap's\u201d contracts call for his smile and service in\nour midst for four years and then some. More power\nto the hardy mariner.\nTHIS YEAR\u2019S BUSINESS\nMany expressions concerning the business outlook\nfor this year have been published, the concensus ap\npearing to be that while there may be a perceptible\nslowing down here and there the general prospect is\nfavorable.\nThere has been some slowing down in automobile\nlines, chemicals, furniture, iron and steel, and a few\nother industries. On the other hand, expansion on a\nlarge scale is promised in public utilities and railroads,\nan unusual program for the contruction of public\nbuildings, roads and other public works is announced\nby the government and various states, and sales efforts\nin practically all lines will be pushed this year with\nvigor. From present indications 1930 should be at least\nan average business year, if not above the average.\nA returned explorer tells that among certain Alas\nkan tribes young girls are starved for several days and\ngiven a good beaten just before they are married. A\nforetaste of the joys to come, as it were.\nPIKES WILL\nCM BN FIGHT\nBAIL\n\nIS S CORED E BY JUDGE WHO\nSAID ATTEMPT MADE IN\nFLUENCE HIM\nLOS ANGELES, Jan., 31, (/P)\u2014\nRepulsed but nat surrendering\nPantages is preparing an appeal on\nJudge Fricke\u2019s refusal to admit him\nto bail.\nAttorney Davis, Pantages\u2019 chief\nI counsel, said a writ of habeas\ncorpus, also the original writ of\napplication, will be filed in the\ncourt of appeals today or Mon\nday in an effort to obtain the\nprisoner's release in order that he\nmay have expert medical care\nfor heart ailment,\ni Court physicians said Pan\ntages condition was due to senile\nranges. The defense said he was\nsuffering from heart disease.\nPantages family and friends\nured by Fricke who said\nthey had attempted to influence\nhim in his decision.\n^he Seward high school bas\nketball team lost to Anchorage\nagain last night, at Anchorage,\naccording to the local report.\nThe score was not ascertained.\nBfilTlilffl\u201d\nTROUBLE SATISFY\nIT'S DOIMONS\nFRENCH COMPROMISE PLAN\nIS DISMISSED RY SPE\nCIAL COMMITTEE\nLONDON. Jan.. 31. f/P)\u2014Chang-!\ning Its plans overnight the five\n\"owrr naval conference went in\nto executive session yesterday af\nternoon for the purpose of\nsmoothing out features and make\n,1\" otir-r procedure.\nThe special committee decid\ned yesterday :>n dismiss the\nFrench compromise o\u2019an for\nof naval power.\nAs the delegates come togeth\ner reports were widespread that\nthe Eritish were having diffi\nculty in satistM-\"'*' it* d^Pniors\nas to representation at the con\nh re jce of committees.\nWhile Miss Cecil Leslie is confin\ned to her home on account of ill\nness, Miss Katherine Neville is em\nployed at the Candy Cottage.\nWOLVES ADVANCING\nReports coming down from the j\nInterior bring word that the ad\nvance guard of wolves, tryant of the j\npredatory killers, is coming over the\nridge from the Interior and slowly\nadvancing toward the coast. This\nmore than any other one thing Is\nthought to be responsible for ap\nparent shortage of fur-bearing ani\nmals, the latter animals having\nbeen driven away from their usual\nhabitante for shelter.\nIF VOL' RAVEN *1 TRIED FRYIL\nBRL\u2019HN\u2019S BABY BFEF. you are\ncertainly missing something.\nResponsible Men j\nWanted\nto represent the Woodmen of\nthe World Life Insurance As\nsociation of Omaha, Nebraska\nA!) forms of life insurance\nwritten by our company,\nwhich hat assets of more than\n$135,000,000 00 If you are\ninterested please write to\nW. A. FRASER, President\nWoodmen oi the World j\nLife Insurance Assn.\ni\nOmaha, Neb.\n<>3IIIHIHHIIC3HIUHII\u00abHC31IIHHliliiniHlimiIII&3inHliHllimillllllllHI3IIIHIHimmillliii!tiirii.iill.i.iilr1.iii.i.i.iiifniii\nI LIBERTY I\n1 THEATER I\nI I\nSATURDAY AT 8 O'CLOCK\nThe Celebrated Actor\nGEORGE BANCROFT\nably supported by\nEVELYN BRENT\nNEIL HAMILTON\nand a brilliant cast in the strong drama\n\u201cThe Showdown\u2019\u2019\nin 8 reels\nTHIS IS A POWERFUL STORY\nLAID IN THE TROPICS\nSomething* different from the usual run of\nbig features. An absorbing story of\nFIVE MEN AND A WOMAN\nat an isolated oil station where the pitiless heat\ngradually brings out different characteristics\nin each resulting in a ve^ thrilling and sen\nsational climax.\nFINE ACTING\nNEW LOCATIONS\nGREAT STORY\nSomething Everybody Will Enjoy\nWith it we will give you an entertaining\nPATHE REVIEW and a FABLE\nOverland\nHotel\nOn the Main Street\nSeward, Alaska\n_ _j\nMEL flOkNEli.\nTHE HOUSE OF QUALITY\nFresh Beef, Pork, Mutton and Poultry\non every boat\nWe are pleased to have you inspect our\nfreezers any time.\nCarstens Packing Co.\n_Phone Mu*11 130 Gus Manthey, Mgr.\nSUBSCRIBE TO THE WEEKLY GATEWAY\ni","height":"28896","width":"21003"}}
